        "created_at": "2025-12-03T12:08:40.258Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"limetree\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"73308\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/4491bb/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> limetree:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is there an official announcement chat in iOS but it just isn’t updated when relevant new releases ship? Or doesn’t it exist in the first place?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The release note chat/channel doesn’t exist yet on iOS. Only on Android and Desktop. It’s also not synced with mobile, so iOS users can see it on Desktop but not on mobile</p>",
